  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "**Why should this feature exist?**\r\n\r\nThere is a lot of overhead in calling from Go into JS via duktape. We can allow JS tracers to specify which opcodes they're interested in and have Geth only dispatch `CaptureState` events for those opcodes. Benchmarks are needed to see if the performance gain is worth it. Same needs to be done for the goja tracer (https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/23773) because there's no go-C context switch.\r\n\r\n**What are the use-cases?**\r\n\r\nE.g. the `prestateTracer`.",
